The United States strongly condemns recent attacks by Boko Haram in Nigeria, Chad, Niger, and Cameroon. The statement offers condolences to the victims and their families and expresses support for the countries' efforts to fight Boko Haram while respecting human rights and the rule of law. The establishment of a Multi-National Joint Task Force is applauded as a promising regional approach to the challenge. The statement emphasizes the importance of swift action to support and operationalize the task force to protect civilians and enhance security in the region. The United States will continue to support initiatives to counter Boko Haram.